reviewText: Video is doable but not new.  The bottom of the video is fuzzy or snowy and somtimes the fuzziness scrolls up and down.

I bought this video to use for workouts, but what I don't like is that everyone in it faces the camera. it is so hard to follow the steps when i have to turn and look over my shoulders to get the steps done right. what ever happened to the older videos where they had their back toward the camera so the steps can be seen properly? this is why people don't like to work out to videos.
This is an incredibly fun way to get a workout. Diane is fantastic!
